README
======

0. Make sure you have ruby, sqlite3, twitter4r and sqlite3-ruby
   installed properly. twitter4r and sqlite3-ruby can be installed by
   RubyGem.

1. Edit the 'config.yml' file. Put your Twitter username and password
   in the right place.

2. Run 'init.rb'. It will create a database file, contains your
   twitter entries.

3. Run 'update.rb' to update your database.
